1 (2) Extreme risk protection provision does not include a domestic violence
2 protection order or an order for involuntary commitment issued under
3 chapters 14 - 07.1 and 25 - 03.1 .
4 2. A person, including a state agency or political subdivision, may not adopt, implement,
5 or enforce an extreme risk protection provision.
6 3. Except for the department of health and human services, a state agency or political
7 subdivision may not use any personnel or funds appropriated by the legislative
8 assembly or any other source of funds to implement any statute, rule, executive order,
9 judicial order, or judicial findings that would have the effect of enforcing an extreme
10 risk protection provision.
11 4. Any person that violates this section is guilty of a class B felony .
